  "text": "The patient data are presented as mean ± SD. Dixon's up-anddown method needs at least six success-failure pairs for statistical analysis [CITATION_1] . ED 50 was defined as the mean of the cross-over doses. Differences in MAP and HR over time for each dose of remifentanil were analyzed with repeated measures analysis of variance (ANOVA) with the Bonferroni multiple-comparison test. A P value less than 0.05 was considered significant. Values are mean ± SD or numbers. ASA: American Society of Anesthesiologists. ",
